<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 12:53PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
Summers and western Monroe Counties through 200 PM EDT...
At 1253 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hinton, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Hinton...
Union...
Sandstone...
Red Sulphur Spring...
Pickaway...
Buck...
and Wayside.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
